Four students of Syokisinga Secondary School in Yatta sub-county drowned in River Athi during a Geography field lesson on Friday afternoon. Those who drowned include one girl and three boys-all in form one who are reported to have attempted to swim in the swollen river. Yatta Sub-County director of education, Stephen Kitungu confirmed the girlâ€™s body had been already retrieved from the river while search for the three others was called off after night fall. He said the exercise will resume Saturday morning.